<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head><meta charset="utf-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"><title>DIY HVAC paperwork</title></head>
<body style="margin:0;padding:0;background-color:#ffffff;font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;color:#27272a;">
  <div style="max-width:600px;margin:0 auto;padding:32px 20px;">
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;">Hey,</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;">Last email. Whether you claim a credit, file a rebate, sell the home later, or make a warranty claim, the paperwork is what makes the install defensible.</p>
    <h2 style="font-size:17px;color:#18181b;margin:28px 0 10px 0;">Keep these records</h2>
    <ul style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.7;margin:0 0 18px 24px;padding:0;">
      <li>Equipment receipts with model numbers and purchase dates.</li>
      <li>Manufacturer certification statements for any credit-eligible equipment.</li>
      <li>Final permit inspection signoff or other placed-in-service date proof.</li>
      <li>Itemized invoices for electrical, refrigerant, or commissioning work you hired out.</li>
      <li>Receipts for specialized materials and tools bought specifically for the install.</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;">For state and utility programs in {{ location.state }}, check DSIRE and read eligibility carefully. Some programs allow self-installs; some require licensed-contractor installation.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 24px 0;"><a href="{{ rebate_lookup_url }}" style="color:#FF6B2B;font-weight:600;text-decoration:underline;">Check {{ location.state }} HVAC and energy-efficiency incentives</a></p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">That is the sequence. Good luck with the install, and keep the receipts.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:20px 0 4px 0;">&mdash; NailTheQuote</p>
